<p>I'm making an application that uses the phone's camera. When I check if the focus is supported, I receive different responses depending on the class:</p>  <p><strong>MediaCapture:</strong></p>  <pre><code>var _mediaCapture = new MediaCapture();  // _mediaCapture initialization  if (_mediaCapture.VideoDeviceController.FocusControl.Supported) // false {     // ... }  if (_mediaCapture.VideoDeviceController.Focus.Capabilities.Supported) // false {     // ... } </code></pre>  <p><strong>PhotoCamera:</strong></p>  <pre><code>PhotoCamera camera;  // camera initialization  if (camera.IsFocusSupported) // TRUE {     // ... } </code></pre>  <p>My cell phone focuses correctly if it uses <code>PhotoCamera</code>, but I need to use <code>MediaCapture</code>.</p>